The paper deals with the dual bin packing problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of combinatorial optimization. The paper also discusses the online version of the problem and its advice complexity, which falls under the category of online algorithms and computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper also presents a PTAS for the problem, which involves approximation algorithms and falls under the category of approximation algorithms and randomized algorithms, which are covered in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
